The paper focuses on data cleaning for predictive models, which is a common task in machine learning and data mining. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DB (Databases), which includes topics related to data management and analysis. The paper also proposes a new approach called ActiveClean, which involves updating the model incrementally instead of re-training, and leverages the structure of the user's model to prioritize cleaning. This suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), which covers topics related to the design and analysis of algorithms that can learn from data. Additionally, the paper mentions several popular models such as linear regression and SVMs, which are commonly used in machine learning and may indicate a focus on cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also evaluates its approach on several real-world datasets, which suggests a focus on cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval), which cover topics related to data analysis and retrieval.
